# ☕ 6-Week Café Digital Solution — Learning Plan

**Stack:** Laravel REST API · MySQL · React (SPA) · React Native Expo  
**Project:** A complete digital solution for a fictional café (menu, orders, bookings, users)

---

## Overview

```mermaid
graph LR
  W1["Week 1\nMySQL + ORM"] --> W2["Week 2\nLaravel API"]
  W2 --> W3["Week 3\nAPI Hardening\n+ Security"]
  W3 --> W4["Week 4\nReact SPA"]
  W4 --> W5["Week 5\nReact Native App"]
  W5 --> W6["Week 6\nTesting + Polish"]
```

---

## Week 1 — Database Design & ORM
**Subject:** Databaseprogrammering (16474)

### Goals
- Design a domain model with **≥ 20 entities** for the café
- Set up MySQL with migrations and seed data
- Use **Eloquent ORM** (Laravel's ORM) for queries and manipulations
- Set up a **MongoDB** document database alongside MySQL and compare the two

### Entity Examples (≥ 20)
`User`, `Role`, `Customer`, `Staff`, `Table`, `Reservation`, `Order`, `OrderItem`,  
`Product`, `Category`, `Ingredient`, `ProductIngredient`, `Recipe`, `Supplier`,  
`Purchase`, `Invoice`, `Payment`, `PaymentMethod`, `Review`, `Promotion`, `PromotionProduct`

### Tasks
- [ ] Create ERD and define all relationships, constraints (FK, unique, not null)
- [ ] Write Laravel migrations for all 20+ entities
- [ ] Seed the database with realistic fake data (Factories + Faker)
- [ ] Write Eloquent queries: eager loading, scopes, aggregations
- [ ] Set up MongoDB collection (e.g. `activity_logs`, `product_reviews`)
- [ ] **Performance comparison:** run benchmark queries on MySQL vs MongoDB for equivalent data, document results in a table

### Deliverable
- ERD diagram
- Migration files + seeders
- ORM query examples (CRUD, joins, aggregations)
- MongoDB vs MySQL comparison doc with performance measurements

---

## Week 2 — Laravel REST API (Core)
**Subject:** Serversideprogrammering (16477)

### Goals
- Build a full **CRUD REST API** in Laravel for the café
- Apply **Repository Pattern**, **IoC** and **Dependency Injection**
- Structure with clean separation of concerns (Controllers → Services → Repositories)

### Tasks
- [ ] Set up Laravel project, configure MySQL connection
- [ ] Generate resource controllers for: `Products`, `Orders`, `Reservations`, `Users`
- [ ] Implement **Repository interfaces** and bind them via **Service Provider** (IoC container)
- [ ] Add **Eloquent resources** (API transformers) for clean JSON output
- [ ] Implement **authentication** with Laravel Sanctum (token-based)
- [ ] Add **async/background processing** with jobs (e.g. send confirmation email on order)

### API Endpoints (examples)

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| GET | `/api/products` | List all menu items |
| POST | `/api/orders` | Place an order |
| GET | `/api/reservations` | List reservations |
| POST | `/api/auth/login` | Login → return token |
| DELETE | `/api/orders/{id}` | Cancel order |

### Deliverable
- Working REST API with full CRUD
- Repository pattern with DI wiring
- Sanctum auth (register/login/logout)

---

## Week 3 — Security & API Hardening
**Subject:** Softwaretest og -sikkerhed (16484)

### Goals
- Secure the API against common attacks
- Implement authentication, hashing, SSL awareness
- Begin security testing

### Tasks
- [ ] **Password hashing** with bcrypt (Laravel's `Hash::make()`) — document MD5 vs bcrypt comparison
- [ ] **Input validation** on all endpoints to prevent **SQL injection** (use Eloquent, never raw input in queries)
- [ ] Add **XSS protection** headers via middleware
- [ ] Configure **HTTPS / SSL** awareness (document how to enable in production)
- [ ] **Role-based authorization** (admin vs customer) using Laravel Gates/Policies
- [ ] Rate limiting on sensitive endpoints (login, order placement)
- [ ] Use **OWASP** checklist — document top 5 risks and mitigations for the café API
- [ ] Run initial security scan with a tool (e.g. **OWASP ZAP** or **Burp Suite Community**)

### Deliverable
- Secured API endpoints
- Security documentation (hashing, SSL, attack mitigations)
- OWASP ZAP scan report

---

## Week 4 — React SPA (Client-Side)
**Subject:** Clientsideprogrammering (16476)

### Goals
- Build a **Single Page Application** in React that consumes the Laravel API
- Full CRUD through the UI, user login/logout

### Tasks
- [ ] Bootstrap React app (Vite + React + TypeScript)
- [ ] Implement **React Router** for SPA navigation
- [ ] Create pages: `Menu`, `Order`, `Reservations`, `Admin Dashboard`, `Login`
- [ ] Connect to Laravel API using **Axios** (handle tokens via interceptors)
- [ ] State management with **React Context** or **Zustand**
- [ ] Admin panel: manage products, view orders, manage reservations (full CRUD)
- [ ] Handle auth flow: login → store token → protected routes

### Key Components

| Component | Description |
|-----------|-------------|
| `MenuPage` | Browse products by category |
| `OrderForm` | Add items, submit order via API |
| `ReservationForm` | Book a table |
| `AdminDashboard` | View + manage all data |
| `AuthContext` | Token management across app |

### Deliverable
- Deployed React SPA (or running locally)
- Full CRUD via API demonstrated in UI
- Protected routes and auth flow

---

## Week 5 — React Native Expo App
**Subject:** App 2 (IT-kravsspecifikation 6239)

### Goals
- Build a **React Native Expo** app for café customers
- Send and receive data from the Laravel API
- Reuse logic/types from the React frontend where possible

### Tasks
- [ ] Initialize Expo app: `npx create-expo-app`
- [ ] Set up **Expo Router** for navigation
- [ ] Screens: `Welcome`, `Menu`, `Order`, `My Orders`, `Login`
- [ ] Fetch menu from API, display items with images
- [ ] Allow customer to place and track orders
- [ ] Login → store Sanctum token with **SecureStore**
- [ ] Push notification on order status update (optional stretch)

### Deliverable
- Working Expo app connecting to Laravel API
- Demo: browse menu → place order → view order status

---

## Week 6 — Testing, Performance & Final Polish
**Subject:** Softwaretest og -sikkerhed (16484)

### Goals
- Write and run a full **test suite** (unit + integration + load)
- Produce a final test plan and release readiness assessment

### Tasks

#### Automated Testing
- [ ] **PHPUnit** unit tests for service/repository classes
- [ ] **Laravel Feature Tests** for all API endpoints (CRUD + auth)
- [ ] **React Testing Library** for key UI components
- [ ] **Cypress** (or Playwright) for end-to-end SPA tests — scripted test scenario

#### Load / Performance Testing
- [ ] **k6** or **Apache JMeter** load test on key API endpoints
- [ ] Document throughput, latency, and identify bottlenecks
- [ ] Compare performance with MongoDB vs MySQL endpoints

#### Test Plan & Release Assessment
- [ ] Write a formal **test plan** covering: functional, security, performance, UX
- [ ] Document **UX test** findings (have someone use the app, note friction points)
- [ ] Assess release readiness: what passes, what needs more work
- [ ] Run final **OWASP ZAP** scan and compare with Week 3 baseline

### Deliverable
- Test suite with passing tests
- Load test report with bottleneck analysis
- Final test plan document
- Release readiness report

